Post-Match Reflections: Netherlands put up a valiant showing with a decent total of 158 for 4 with Colin Ackerman scoring 41 of just 26 balls.
The Protea batters fell one after the other with no momentum or belief to hold the bat let alone reach the target.
The Proteas lost to the Netherlands by 13 runs, succumbing to a thirteen run defeat at the hands of the Dutch Brigade.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The all-so-familiar feeling of desolation had once again engulfed the South African faithful.
The match was played on an Adelaide surface which was slow but certainly not unplayable.
